<div class="page-shell page-shell--public">
  <%= render "shared/public_topbar",
    menu_id: "onboarding-menu",
    nav_label: "Onboarding navigation",
    nav_links: [
      { label: "Home", path: root_path, active: false },
      { label: "Privacy", path: privacy_policy_path },
      { label: "Terms", path: terms_of_service_path }
    ],
    action_container_class: ("nav-actions-auth" unless @signed_in),
    action_links: if @signed_in
      [{ label: "Open workspace", path: dashboard_path, class_name: "mini-button mini-button-primary" }]
    else
      [
        { label: "Sign in", path: browser_sign_in_path, class_name: "mini-button" },
        { label: google_only_auth_mode? ? "Start with Google" : "Create account", path: public_auth_entry_path, class_name: "mini-button mini-button-primary" }
      ]
    end %>

  <section class="section-card">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="eyebrow">Onboarding</div>
      <h1>Write, capture, organize, enrich, and wipe the page clean.</h1>
      <p>The notebook is reusable. The context is not. Inkcreate preserves the history even when the physical page gets reused.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flow">
      <article class="flow-step">
        <div class="mini-label">1</div>
        <strong>Learn the flow</strong>
        <p>Understand how reusable pages map to projects, days, and durable capture history.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="flow-step">
        <div class="mini-label">2</div>
        <strong>Delay camera permission</strong>
        <p>Ask for camera access only when the user taps into the capture workflow.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="flow-step">
        <div class="mini-label">3</div>
        <strong>Create your first project</strong>
        <p>Set up a long-running workspace or skip straight to daily capture.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="flow-step">
        <div class="mini-label">4</div>
        <strong>Optional backup</strong>
        <p>Connect Google Drive later when you decide cloud backup is worth it.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-row">
      <% if @signed_in %>
        <%= link_to "Open workspace", dashboard_path, class: "button button-primary" %>
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to(google_only_auth_mode? ? "Start with Google" : "Create account", public_auth_entry_path, class: "button button-primary") %>
      <% end %>
      <%= link_to "Install guidance", install_path, class: "button button-secondary" %>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%= render "shared/public_footer" %>
</div>
